          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertOverpunch10ToDecimal",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a string representation of a number with overpunch characters into a decimal value. Overpunch characters are used in certain legacy systems, such as mainframes, to encode the sign of a number within the last digit of a numeric string. This function interprets these characters and converts the string into a decimal number with the correct sign."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is considered medium due to the need to handle specific character encoding (overpunch) and convert it into a numeric format. This involves understanding the mapping of overpunch characters to their respective numeric values and signs, which adds a layer of complexity beyond simple string manipulation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
